## 2. Feature folder layout

> Route entries live separately in `lib/screens/[name]/top.dart` (thin auto_route wrappers, ~10 lines) and are not detailed here — see existing code for the pattern.

```
features/[name]/
├── domain/                                     # 🎯 innermost layer — enterprise-wide business rules (no Flutter / Firebase / Proto deps)
│   ├── entity/
│   │   └── [name]_entity.dart                  # data + business rules, use @freezed for entity
│   └── repository/
│       └── [name]_repository.dart              # interface ONLY, no impl — the key to Dependency Inversion (Domain owns the contract, Infra implements it)
├── usecase/                                    # OPTIONAL — add when business logic required
│   └── place_bet_usecase.dart                  # one file per user action, named by intent
├── provider/                                   # Riverpod wiring (not a layer). Default: one file per provider; group only when tightly coupled
│   ├── [name]_repository_provider.dart         # injects NameRepository (DI binding)
│   ├── [name]_provider.dart                    # read-only data — wraps a repo call as AsyncValue (e.g. teamTrophyProvider)
│   ├── [name]_notifier.dart                    # mutable page state — exposes methods to update it
│   └── place_bet_usecase_provider.dart         # OPTIONAL — one file per action usecase
├── presentation/
│   ├── widget/                                 # pure presentational components (no ref.watch)
│   │   └── [name]_card.dart
│   └── view/                                   # page-level widgets that wire up providers via ref.watch
│       └── [name]_page_view.dart
└── infrastructure/                             # split into subfolders when the feature gets large
    ├── repository/
    │   └── [name]_repository_impl.dart         # the actual impl — talks to API / Firebase / etc. (outer layer)
    ├── datasource/                             # OPTIONAL
    │   └── [name]_service.dart                 # raw gRPC / Firebase calls
    ├── dto/                                    # OPTIONAL
    │   └── [name]_dto.dart                     # DTO (Data Transfer Object) — only when it differs from entity
    └── mapper/                                 # OPTIONAL
        └── [name]_mapper.dart                  # DTO ↔ NameEntity translation — only when the conversion logic gets complex
```

**Notifier naming**: new files → `[name]_notifier.dart`. Legacy names (e.g. `*_selection_provider.dart`) are fine.

