## 4. Clean Architecture — Dependency Rule

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph Outer["Outer (volatile)"]
        P[Presentation<br/>widget · view]
        I[Infrastructure<br/>repository impl · API clients · Firebase]
    end
    subgraph Middle["Middle"]
        U[UseCase<br/>application logic · orchestration]
    end
    subgraph Inner["Inner (stable)"]
        D[Domain<br/>entities · business rules · repository interfaces]
    end

    P -->|depends on| U
    U -->|depends on| D
    I -->|implements interfaces from| D

    classDef inner fill:#ffe0a6,stroke:#b07a00,color:#000,stroke-width:2px
    classDef middle fill:#d4e4f1,stroke:#2d5a7a,color:#000
    classDef outer fill:#f1e4d4,stroke:#7a5a2d,color:#000
    class D inner
    class U middle
    class P,I outer
```

> Riverpod providers are DI wiring, not a layer of their own — see the `provider/` note in §2.